para_trans: Government Decision No: ABVI-2023 / Q. No.1999 / Q.6
The ECCE Steering Committee shall have the following functions: -
1) National Education Policy-2020 and Early Childhood Care and Education for Anganwadis (ECCE)
Effective implementation of this policy for Anganwadis taking into account the prevailing orders in the matter.
For this to happen, the committee should make recommendations.
(2) No recommendations may be implemented without the approval of the Government.
Duration of the Committee. - The term of the Committee shall be 1 year.
4. Non-official members of the School Education Department if they have constituted such a committee.
The non-governmental members of the committee should be given the same benefits as they are given. or otherwise, or
No benefits will be admissible to non-official members. Accordingly, the Commissioner, Integrated
Child Development Services Scheme, Navi Mumbai should take necessary action.
The Government decision is available on the Government of Maharashtra website www.maharashtra.gov.in.
